	section "The I2C-bus protocol" {
		details : <text>Spec text: 3 The
I2C-bus
protocol </text>;
		section "Standard-mode, Fast-mode and Fast-mode Plus" {
			details : <text>Spec text: Standard-mode, Fast-mode and Fast-mode Plus
I2C-bus
protocols </text>;
			coverage "chk_controllerSpec" {
				is_check : "TRUE";
				ep_CovChkTc : "CHK";
				item_details : <text>Spec text:  A controller is the device which initiates a data
transfer on the bus and generates the clock signals to permit that transfer. </text>;
				ep_annotref "r7bc58a57164cd219db9e6c3664375ee2" {
					ep_ref : "UM10204.pdf/a853a24f993ce3bb6c1df8d09baae9b0c";
				}
			}
			coverage "chk_targetSpec" {
				is_check : "TRUE";
				ep_CovChkTc : "CHK";
				item_details : <text>Spec text: t that time,
any device addressed is considered a target. </text>;
				ep_annotref "r427aa1b96a7ddb7f638a307aeb52b52c" {
					ep_ref : "UM10204.pdf/aa083e41e69bb554421ff3e2a79dca746";
				}
			}
			coverage "tst_writeTransaction" {
				is_check : "TRUE";
				ep_CovChkTc : "TC";
				item_details : <text>Spec text: Suppose microcontroller A wants to send information to microcontroller B:
• microcontroller A (controller), addresses microcontroller B (target)
• microcontroller A (controller-transmitter), sends data to microcontroller B (target-
receiver)
• microcontroller A terminates the transfer. </text>;
				ep_annotref "re2e375b16eef534bf4e6f60ec2fd1354" {
					ep_ref : "UM10204.pdf/ac1b5f1e248d4892052627d91e861fce8";
				}
			}
			coverage "tst_readTransaction" {
				is_check : "TRUE";
				ep_CovChkTc : "TC";
				item_details : <text>Spec text:  If microcontroller A wants to receive information from microcontroller B:
• microcontroller A (controller) addresses microcontroller B (target)
• microcontroller A (controller-receiver) receives data from microcontroller B (target-
transmitter)
• microcontroller A terminates the transfer. </text>;
				ep_annotref "r261b12cf5f256449ad364c4fc57f5a28" {
					ep_ref : "UM10204.pdf/ab5e09b9db16fcd1d39a75b11ecf33423";
				}
			}
			coverage "chk_controllerGenTiming" {
				is_check : "TRUE";
				ep_CovChkTc : "CHK";
				item_details : <text>Spec text: Even in this case, the controller (microcontroller A) generates the timing and terminates
the transfer. </text>;
				ep_annotref "rb712a966b3a74602f837d6f2dceb8049" {
					ep_ref : "UM10204.pdf/affe15da7a5755d44e20a84ddd19c08af";
				}
			}
