NXP Semiconductors
UM10204
I2C-bus
specification and user manual
a STOP condition (P) generated by the controller. </text>;
				ep_annotref "r038aab40b710f9a832e14c5b6e01fa7d" {
					ep_ref : "UM10204.pdf/a3af62d5b2b8dc2098739d8fb0bf8db5e";
				}
			}
			coverage "chk_RWBit(0 = write)" {
				is_check : "TRUE";
				ep_CovChkTc : "CHK";
				item_details : "Spec text:  a ‘zero’ indicates a transmission (WRITE),";
				ep_annotref "r01a81df379ea9ed128d8af6f319ca8d9" {
					ep_ref : "UM10204.pdf/af47f19d4b03ec93f0d808517a264ab8e";
				}
			}
			coverage "chk_RWBit(1 = read)" {
				is_check : "TRUE";
				ep_CovChkTc : "CHK";
				item_details : <text>Spec text: a ‘one’ indicates
a request for data (READ) </text>;
				ep_annotref "r68676075eb1956f8bb736720e4e93ca1" {
					ep_ref : "UM10204.pdf/a2f9931281ccea2d7706032dc52e630b1";
				}
			}
			coverage "chk_repeatedStartToKeepBusBusy" {
				is_check : "TRUE";
				ep_CovChkTc : "CHK";
				item_details : <text>Spec text: However, if a controller still wishes to
communicate on the bus, it can generate a repeated START condition (Sr) and address
another target without first generating a STOP condition. </text>;
				ep_annotref "ra237809decec609da376d3d1b06e5537" {
					ep_ref : "UM10204.pdf/a04f669fd02c3e3089ae00944ef162713";
				}
			}
			coverage "tst_writeTransaction" {
				is_check : "TRUE";
				ep_CovChkTc : "TC";
				item_details : <text>Spec text:  Controller-transmitter transmits to target-receiver. The transfer direction is not changed
(see Figure 11). The target receiver acknowledges each byte. </text>;
				ep_annotref "r7f6cabe882c47217670e3edd3a14fc02" {
					ep_ref : "UM10204.pdf/aa1590b69ff6408461d65353514d81b90";
				}
			}
			coverage "tst_readTransaction" {
				is_check : "TRUE";
				ep_CovChkTc : "TC";
				item_details : <text>Spec text:  Controller reads target immediately after first byte (see Figure 12). At the moment of
the first acknowledge, the controller-transmitter becomes a controller-receiver and the
target-receiver becomes a target-transmitter. This first acknowledge is still generated
by the target. The controller generates subsequent acknowledges. The STOP condition
is generated by the controller, which sends a not-acknowledge (A) just before the
STOP condition.</text>;
				ep_annotref "rda32d94ea7c04fc8f9d72a8c0322c409" {
					ep_ref : "UM10204.pdf/ad86c11e2d07648b09e1761b81b88884e";
				}
			}
			coverage "tst_combinedFormat" {
				is_check : "TRUE";
				ep_CovChkTc : "TC";
				item_details : <text>Spec text: • Combined format (see Figure 13). During a change of direction within a transfer,
the START condition and the target address are both repeated, but with the R/W bit
reversed. If a controller-receiver sends a repeated START condition, it sends a not-
acknowledge (A) just before the repeated START condition. </text>;
				ep_annotref "r1247e47d54276580df413e9883032ff5" {
					ep_ref : "UM10204.pdf/a96eb21595c0dd2cd75605b6ba7e1c0dc";
				}
			}
			coverage "tst_combinedFormatForMemoryAddressing" {
				is_check : "TRUE";
				ep_CovChkTc : "TC";
				item_details : <text>Spec text:  Combined formats can be used, for example, to control a serial memory. The internal
memory location must be written during the first data byte. After the START condition
and target address is repeated, data can be transferred. </text>;
				ep_annotref "r17e064491a8f666891d602a1f080df89" {
					ep_ref : "UM10204.pdf/a6cd7acec0be6e4d285248fdb2a047c41";
				}
			}
			coverage "tst_memoryHandlingDesignedByEachDevice" {
				is_check : "TRUE";
				ep_CovChkTc : "TC";
				item_details : <text>Spec text: . All decisions on auto-increment or decrement of previously accessed memory
locations, etc., are taken by the designer of the device. </text>;
				ep_annotref "r75739091ef0f6909f709675da67db7a4" {
					ep_ref : "UM10204.pdf/aaf2fce49a2c2557edfdaf351e4338dd1";
				}
			}
			coverage "chk_resetAfterStart" {
				is_check : "TRUE";
				ep_CovChkTc : "CHK";
				item_details : <text>Spec text: I2C-bus
compatible devices must reset their bus logic on receipt of a START or
repeated START condition such that they all anticipate the sending of a target
